WorkItem.Description:
If you like to organise your files different than suggested and want to define PHPEXCEL_ROOT, it won't work.
 
See file PHPExec.php on line 29 - 33. It doesn;t make any sense. This would:
 
/** PHPExcel root directory */
if (!defined('PHPEXCEL_ROOT')) {
	define('PHPEXCEL_ROOT', dirname(__FILE__) . '/');
}
require(PHPEXCEL_ROOT . 'PHPExcel/Autoloader.php');
